<br>
I have asked and volunteered to help with the calendar before when moderators were needed.  But I was not accepted. I do not have the power to alter the calendar. <br>
<br>
I have asked on many occasions that people have the courtesy and decency to respect the calendar and follow the rules that govern it.  I asked  as nicely as possible and people still DID NOT hear me.<br>
<br>
I got TIRED of talking to a wall.<br>
<br>
So I did what I (me as raid leader) can do to try and STOP the flagrant disregard of the calendar.  I posted CONSEQUENCES that will happen if individuals violate the &quot;2-week&quot; rule. This is something that I (as a raid leader) will do. If I stood alone, I was ready for that. If others supported my actions, great. If other raid leaders followed my example, so much the better. The consequences are heavier. <br>
<br>
Almost all open, semi and closed raid leaders try to honor the calendar so that the posting of raids on days could be as FAIR as possible. I did not say &quot;EVERYONE&quot; followed it but the VAST majority did. <br>
<br>
You will ALWAYS have the uber guilds having their own agenda and I know some don't even BOTHER looking at the calendar. I cannot do anything as an individual to stop them. They have the manpower and forces to pretty much do what they want. However, in my dealings with them I have always found a way to compromise and still raid. Talking to their raid leaders, I have always found some form of communication possible and beneficial. <br>
<br>
What I want to do is find a solution to the flagrant disregard of calendar. True... the &quot;2-week&quot; rule is NOT something everyone has to follow. As we can see almost daily, it was frequently broken.  But it is the BEST and FAIREST rule we have to posting and raiding. <br>
<br>
Anyone can disregard the &quot;2-week&quot; rule. There was no stopping them. But now, IF they do... there are CONSEQUENCES. <br>
<br>
A rule is not a &quot;rule&quot; unless it is enforced.  IF there are no consequences to breaking that rule, it's not much of a rule. Why do you follow the rules in real life? It is because you were brought up to and there are consequences to breaking them. <br>
<br>
We as a community MUST enforce the following of the  &quot;2-week&quot; rule.  Who else will?<br>
<br>
I'm sorry that you don't agree with my actions but you don't have to... these are MY actions. <br>
<br>
I want to THANK everyone that DOES support this. The more raid leaders that support this, the heavier the consequences for violating what everyone has tried to uphold: respect and courtesy of others on the calendar.<br>
